This edition of the T20 World Cup, whose inaugural edition took place in 2007, was originally supposed to be held in 2020. However, as the entire world battled with a pandemic in 2020, it was decided by the game’s governing body, the International Cricket Council, that the tournament would be postponed. T20 World Cup 2022 Teams

All the major teams which were a part of the last edition of the T20 World Cup will be a part of this tournament in Australia. The hosts – Australia, by virtue of being the host nation, get a direct entry into the World Cup. From Asia, India and Pakistan will be joined by Bangladesh and Afghanistan. New Zealand, England, and South Africa will also be participating in the T20 World Cup 2022.

These eight teams will straightaway move to the Super 12s. To join them in Super 12s, eight more teams will contest in two groups. Out of those eight teams, four have already booked a place by having qualified for the Super 12s in the last year’s T20 World Cup. Those four teams are Sri Lanka, West Indies, Namibia, and Scotland. They will be joined by UAE and Ireland who have emerged as the top two teams from Qualifier A. Two more teams which top Qualifier B will join them in the qualifiers.
